<article>
    <h1>Sand&#xAD;storm In An Hour&#xAD;glass ThisCon&#xAD;nect: Thread&#xAD;ing Worlds Dancers&#x2019; Locker 2020</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Just like a sand­storm in an hour­glass might per­suade us to shift our per­cep­tion of time, the art­works by Joo Choon Lin, Jax­ton Su and Se­bas­tian Mary Tay in­vite view­ers into their “hour­glasses”. Lin is a visual artist, di­rec­tor, com­poser and film-maker. Su works with paint­ing, in­stal­la­tion and video art, while Tay is an in­ter­dis­ci­pli­nary artist. Cu­rated by Poland-based artist Mag­dalen Chua and sup­ported by the Na­tional Arts Coun­cil, the Arts Fund and The Glas­gow School of Art Cre­ative Net­work.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The Sub­sta­tion, 45 Ar­me­nian Street MRT: City Hall WHEN: Till Sun , noon to 8pm AD­MIS­SION: Free</p>
    <p>INFO: art­sre­pub­lic.sg</p>
    <p>This mul­ti­dis­ci­plinary ex­hi­bi­tion is held in con­junc­tion with Sui­cide Pre­ven­tion Aware­ness Month and fea­tures works by so­cial artist duo Hunny & Lummy (Hun Ming Kwang and Quinn Lum). The two works, Tip­ping Point and I Feel You, fo­cus on the theme of hu­man con­nec­tions. The show is a pre­lude to an ex­hi­bi­tion</p>
    <p>Pre­sented by Fron­tier Dance­land, Dancers’ Locker re­turns with a dig­i­tal ver­sion fea­tur­ing six short films by com­pany artists Ma Yueru (Singapore), Tan Xin Yen (Malaysia), Sam­man­tha Yue (Singapore),</p>
    <p>Kon­rad Plak (Poland), Mark Robles (Philip­pines) and Keigo Nozaki (Ja­pan). Themes and top­ics range from do­mes­tic anx­i­eties and cir­cuit breaker mea­sures to mor­tal­ity and fa­mil­ial ties. The artists will present works-in-progress for the screen­ing, fol­lowed by a live Q&A ses­sion. WHERE: Zoom WHEN: To­mor­row, 8pm AD­MIS­SION: Free; do­na­tions are wel­come INFO: art­sre­pub­lic.sg</p>
    <p>A Lover’s Con­certo Episodes 1 & 2</p>
    <p>Cou­ples of dif­fer­ent gen­er­a­tions who all met at the City Con­tem­po­rary Dance Com­pany (CCDC) will per­form in this work. Es­tab­lished 41 years ago, CCDC has per­formed to au­di­ences in Hong Kong and other parts of the world, and pre­sented more than 200 orig­i­nal works to crit­i­cal ac­claim. WHERE: Sis­tic Live WHEN: Episode 1: live stream on Sun, 8pm, view­able till Sept 15; Episode 2: live stream on</p>
    <p>Oct 18, 8pm, view­able till Oct 20 AD­MIS­SION: $10 INFO: sis­tic.com.sg/ events/sllover102­0</p>


</article>

